9i\u017eka'''\n| style=\"background:#8ab8e6;\"| '''TOP 8'''\n| style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|\t\n|style=\"background:#8ab8e6;\"| '''Elim'''\t\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"background:#919191;\"|\t\t\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccc;\" rowspan=\"6\"|'''Semi-<br />Final 2'''\n| style=\"background:pink;\"| {{flagicon|Slovakia|size=15px}} R\u00e9ka Ballov\u00e1\n| style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|\n| style=\"background:#ccc;\" rowspan=\"6\"|'''Elim'''\n| style=\"background:#919191;\" colspan=\"14\" rowspan=\"6\"|\t\n|-\t\n| style=\"background:pink;\"| {{flagicon|Czech Republic|size=15px}} Veronika Vrublov\u00e1\n| style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink;\"| {{flagicon|Czech Republic|size=15px}} Melinda No\u00e1kov\u00e1\n| style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink;\"| {{flagicon|Czech Republic|size=15px}} Alena Shirmanova\n| style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink;\"| {{flagicon|Czech Republic|size=15px}} Karol\u00edna P\u0159ibylov\u00e1\n| style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"background:pink;\"| {{flagicon|Slovakia|size=15px}} Nikol Kassell\n| style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccc;\" rowspan=\"6\"|'''Semi-<br />Final 1'''\n| style=\"background:cyan;\"| {{flagicon|Slovakia|size=15px}} Vojt\u011bch Dzudza\n| style=\"background:#ccc;\" rowspan=\"6\"|'''Elim'''\n| style=\"background:#919191;\" colspan=\"15\" rowspan=\"6\"|\t\n|-\n| style=\"background:cyan;\"| {{flagicon|Slovakia|size=15px}} Peter Farka\u0161ovsk\u00fd\n|-\n| style=\"background:cyan;\"| {{flagicon|Slovakia|size=15px}} Samuel Sleziak\n|-\n| style=\"background:cyan;\"| {{flagicon|Czech Republic|size=15px}} Jan Tejkal\n|-\n| style=\"background:cyan;\"| {{flagicon|Czech Republic|size=15px}} Marek Po\u0161ta\n|-\n| style=\"background:cyan;\"| {{flagicon|Czech Republic|size=15px}} Patricio Malundo\n|}\n</center>\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://superstar.nova.cz Official Czech homepage hosted by Nova]\n*[http://superstar.markiza.sk Official Slovak homepage hosted by Mark\u00edza]\n{{Idol series}}\n{{SuperStar}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cesko Slovenska SuperStar 2015}}\n[[Category:SuperStar (Czech and Slovak TV series)|Season 03]]\n[[Category:2010s Czech television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Slovak television series]]\n[[Category:2015 Czech television seasons]]\n[[Category:2015 Slovak television seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox reality music competition\n|series        = \u010cesko Slovensk\u00e1 SuperStar\n|season        = 4\n|first_aired   = August 30, 2015\n|last_aired    = \n|judges        = [[Ond\u0159ej Soukup]]<br>[[Marta Jandov\u00e1]]<br>[[Pavol Habera]]<br>[[Kl\u00e1ra Vytiskov\u00e1]]\n|host          = Martin \"Pyco\" Rausch<br>[[Jitka Nov\u00e1\u010dkov\u00e1]]\n|cohost        =\n|broadcaster   = [[TV Nova (Czech Republic)|Nova]]<br>[[Mark\u00edza]]\n|finalsvenue   = [[Barrandov Studios]]\n|image         = \n|caption       = \n|winner-name   = [[Emma Drobn\u00e1]]\n|winner-origin = [[Nov\u00e9 Mesto nad V\u00e1hom]], [[Slovakia]] \n|winner-genre  = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n|winner-song   = [[Fix You]]\n|runner-name   = \u0160t\u011bp\u00e1n Urban\n|last          = \u010cesko Slovensk\u00e1 SuperStar 2013\n|next          = \u010cesko Slovensk\u00e1 SuperStar 2018\n|year          = 2015\n}}\n\n'''''\u010cesko Slovensk\u00e1 SuperStar''''' (English: '''''Czech&Slovak SuperStar''''') is the joint [[Czech Republic|Czech]]-[[Slovakia|Slovak]] version of [[Idol series]]' ''[[Pop Idol]]'' merged from ''[[\u010cesko hled\u00e1 SuperStar]]'' and ''[[Slovensko h\u013ead\u00e1 SuperStar]]'' which previous to that had three individual seasons each.\nThe fourth season premiered in autumn 2015 with castings held in [[Prague]], [[Brno]], [[Ostrava]], [[\u017dilina]], [[Bratislava]] and [[Ko\u0161ice]]. It is broadcast on two channels: \u00ab[[Nova (Czech TV)|TV Nova]]\u00bb (Czech Republic) and \u00ab[[Mark\u00edza]]\u00bb (Slovakia) which have also been the broadcast stations for the individual seasons. Also both hosts have been their hosts countries before as have been three out of the four judges.\n\n==Regional auditions==\nAuditions were held in [[Bratislava]], [[Ko\u0161ice]], [[Prague]], [[Ostrava]], [[\u017dilina]] and [[Brno]] in the summer of 2015.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"text-align:Center; background:#ccc;\"\n|'''Audition City'''\n|'''Date'''\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||[[Ko\u0161ice]], [[Slovakia]]\n||May 16, 2015\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||[[\u017dilina]], [[Slovakia]]\n||May 17, 2015\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||[[Ostrava]], [[Czech Republic]]\n||May 23, 2015\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||[[Brno]], [[Czech Republic]]\n||May 24, 2015\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||[[Bratislava]], [[Slovakia]]\n||May 30, 2015\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||[[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]]\n||June 5\u20136, 2015\n|}\n\n==Ve\u013ek\u00fd v\u00fdber==\nIn Ve\u013ek\u00fd v\u00fdber where 100 contestants. The contestants first emerged on stage in groups of 9 or 10 but performed solo unaccompanied, and those who did not impress the judges were cut after the group finished their individual performances. 40 made it to the next round held in beach. Contestnats will sing in duet. Next round is Dlouh\u00e1 cesta. 20 contestants made it to the Semi-final.\n\n==Semi-final==\n20 semifinalists will revealed in October when the show premiered on screen. Ten boys and ten girls competed for a spot in the top 8. From each semi final 4 contestant will made it to the final. Public will choose one contestant and other three will be chosen by jury.\n\n===Top 10 - Boys===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ \n! scope=\"col\"| Order\n! scope=\"col\"| Contestant\n! scope=\"col\"| Song <small>(original artist)</small>\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n|- \n| 1\n| Vojt\u011bch Dzudza\n| \"